## Full Node Workflow (iSupply AI Studio)

The canonical order for a complete commercial shoot:

```
STEP 1 — Upload product reference photo
  → UploadNode
  → Set name + tags matching Agent 4's product keywords
  → App auto-matches by tag when prompt mentions those words

STEP 2 — Generate model reference sheet  [recommended]
  → ModelCreationNode
  → Paste Agent 2's Model Block into Description field
  → Generate → save to library → upload composite as asset with model tags

STEP 3 — Generate background plate (single or composite)
  → SettingNode
  → Paste Agent 3's Setting Block
  → Single-angle: standard mode, one plate, one camera direction
  → Multi-angle: select Multi-Angle mode, choose panel count (2/3/4),
    generates all camera directions of the location in one composite frame
  → Do NOT include quality tags — the node appends them automatically
  → Temperature 0.6, fixed seed — saved alongside the plate/composite
  → Generate → output auto-saves to library with all angle tags combined
  → Connect SettingNode output to ALL PromptNodes for this concept

STEP 4 — Generate the scene
  → PromptNode (single) or CarouselPromptNode (multi-slide)
  → Paste Director's Master Prompt (or carousel slide prompts)
  → Enter API Config values in right panel (or let auto-detect fill them)
  → All reference images auto-attach via tag matching
  → Click Generate

STEP 5 — Explore variants
  → OutputNode Seed Explorer: try +1, +2, +7, +13
  → Adjust temperature ±0.1 for mood shifts
  → Save keepers to library → export or download
```

